value.value: Seconds times nanograms per milliliter.
Seconds times nanomoles per milliliter.
Seconds times picograms per milliliter.
Seconds times picomoles per milliliter.

label.value: Steady State Total Body Clearance by Fraction of Dose Absorbed

value.value: An estimate of the total body clearance at steady state, where F is the fraction of dose absorbed.

label.value: Steady State Total Body Clearance Rate

value.value: An estimate of the total body clearance at steady state.
The number of time points used in computing Lambda z.
The sum of urine volumes that are collected over time.
The time required for 50% of a drug to be excreted from a body tissue.
A blood smear technique used to make a thick blood smear on a microscope slide which is generally used to look for blood parasites such as those causing malaria.

label.value: Stage IIB Soft Tissue Sarcoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIB includes: (T2a, N0, M0, G2); (T2b, N0, M0, G2).  T2a: Superficial tumor more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.  T2b: Deep tumor more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  G2: Grade 2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)
A blood smear technique used to make a thin blood smear on a microscope slide which is generally used to look for blood parasites such as those causing malaria.
The correlation between time (X) and log concentration (Y) for the points used in the estimation of lambda z.
The time of the last measurable (positive) concentration.

label.value: Time of Maximum Observed Excretion Rate

value.value: TThe midpoint of a collection interval associated with the maximum observed excretion rate.
The time prior to the first measurable (non-zero) concentration.
The time of minimum concentration sampled during a dosing interval.
The principal purpose of the trial.
The auxiliary purpose of the trial.

A microscopy staining method that utilizes a modified trichrome stain to determine the presence of microspordial, sporulating species. The staining method utilizes chromotrope 2R, a red acidic dye, the counterstain fast green, and phosphotungstic acid.

A microscopy staining method that utilizes the Romanowsky stains, eosin and methylene blue, solubilized in methanol. In this staining protocol, methanol is also utilized as a fixative agent prior to staining.

label.value: Stage IA Soft Tissue Sarcoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IA includes: (T1a, N0, M0, G1, GX); (T1b, N0, M0, G1, GX).  T1a: Superficial tumor 5 cm or less in greatest dimension.  T1b: Deep tumor 5 cm or less in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  G1: Grade 1.  GX: Grade cannot be assessed. (AJCC 7th ed.)

A spectrometric method that determines the type and concentration of elements or chemicals in a sample, based upon the principle that each element emits fluorescent light of a particular wavelength when exposed to an X-ray.

label.value: Ziehl Neelsen Acid Fast Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy acid fast staining method that utilizes Ziehl-Neelsen carbol fuchsin, acid alcohol and methylene blue, to determine the presence of acid fast microorganisms. This acid fast staining technique requires heating during the primary staining step involving the carbol fuchsin.
The cumulative amount of substance recovered from a specimen.
A complete diagnostic examination of a patient including history taking, physical examinations, laboratory tests, and medical imaging.

label.value: Stage IA Breast Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1, N0, M0.  T1: Tumor 20 mm or less in greatest dimension.  T1 includes T1mi. T1mi: Tumor 1 mm or less in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No clinical or radiographic evidence of distant metastasis.  M0 includes M0(i+).  (AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IB Breast Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IB includes: (T0, N1mi, M0); (T1, N1mi, M0).  T0: No evidence of primary tumor.  T1: Tumor 20 mm or less in greatest dimension.  T1 includes T1mi. T1mi: Tumor 1 mm or less in greatest dimension.  N1mi: Nodal micrometastases.  M0: No clinical or radiographic evidence of distant metastasis.  M0 includes M0(i+).  (AJCC 7th Ed.)

A light microscopic technique in which the light that does not come into contact with the structures or details of interest is subtracted from the ocular image. This yields an image in which the structures or details are alight while the areas where the structures or details are absent are dark.
Any healthcare organization, institution, facility or provider directly involved in conducting or facilitating a particular clinical trial.

label.value: CDISC SDTM Pharmacokinetic Parameter Short Name Terminology

value.value: Terminology associated with the pharmacokinetic parameter test code codelist of the Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium (CDISC) Study Data Tabulation Model (SDTM).
An inflatable reservoir that is used to expand the remaining breast skin after a mastectomy and prior to surgical reconstruction.

label.value: Area Under Excretion Rate Curve All

value.value: The area under the excretion rate curve (AURC) from time zero to the time of the last observation, regardless of whether the last observation is a measurable concentration or not.
A PCR-based method for differentiating M. tuberculosis strains based on the number of tandem repeats of the Mycobacterial Interspersed Repetitive Unit.
A PCR-based method for differentiating M. tuberculosis strains based on amplification of the polymorphic direct repeat locus.
A function that transforms the colors of one (source) image to the colors of another (target) image.
An image composed of pixels with varying intensities of a single color.
A color map composed of shades of gray, varying from black at the weakest intensity to white at the strongest.

A color map composed of warm and cool colors, varying from blue at the weakest intensity to red at the strongest and with a neutral color at the midpoint. It is useful for data where the sign is important.
A color map that varies from red at one extreme to yellow at the other extreme.
A color map that varies from cyan at one extreme to magenta at the other extreme.

label.value: Stage III Soft Tissue Sarcoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: (T2a, T2b, N0, M0, G3); (Any T, N1, M0, Any G).  T2a: Superficial tumor more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.  T2b: Deep tumor more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  N1: Regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  G3: Grade 3.  There is no T2a for the pathologic group. (AJCC 7th ed.)
A graph in which the edges are not ordered, and therefore, are symmetric.
A pictorial representation of a graph on plane, for visualization of certain properties of the graph or of the data modeled by the graph.
A type of graph that uses a focus node with other nodes arranged in concentric circles around the focus to illustrate the central node's degree of connectivity to the other nodes.
A type of graph where all nodes are placed on the perimeter of a circle and are joined by lines passing within the circle. It is especially useful for illustrating networks.
A type of graph similar to a radial layout, but compressed to fit rapidly-branching networks.
A shape similar to a rectangle but with corners that resemble an arc of a circle.
